Extract model output file data

Extract model output file data from an xpdb object.

get_file(xpdb, file = NULL, problem = NULL, subprob = NULL)

Arguments

xpdb

An xpose_data object from which the model output file data will be extracted.
file

Name of the file to be extracted from the xpdb e.g. 'run001.ext'.
problem

The problem to be used, by default returns the last one for each file.
subprob

The subproblem to be used, by default returns the last one for each file.

Value

A tibble for single file or a named list for multiple files.

See also

xpose_data, read_nm_files

Examples

# Single file (returns a tibble)
ext_file <- get_file(xpdb_ex_pk, 'run001.ext')
ext_file
